Friday's funeral mass for John Paul II was briefly interrupted when many in the crowd began chanting "santo, santo" repeatedly.
Others held up large banners demanding "santo subito" (sainthood now) for a man who created more saints than all his predecessors put together.
The Catholic Church has three steps to sainthood.
First is a ruling that the person concerned has led an exemplary life.
The next stage is beatification, which requires proof of a miracle as a result of his intercession.
The final stage, canonisation, requires at least one more miracle.
