"He knew his health was in decline and that there was a danger he would be unable to communicate."
The indefatigable John Paul II, who completed 104 foreign trips over his 26 year reign, would not have wanted to continue "if he would be unable to perform," Connell said.
"He had a very profound sense of responsibility."
